Cezanne (DK Art Book)
Dorling Kindersley | 1999 | ISBN: 0751307327 | English | 146 pages | PDF | 25.7 MB

Examines the life and work of Paul Cezanne, through more than 300 colour reproductions of his paintings which are documented and placed in their social and historical context. This book is one of a series which explores art from the end of the Middle Ages to the beginning of the 20th century
